Simple Calculator

This is a simple command-line calculator application built with TypeScript. It allows users to perform basic arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division) on two numbers.

How to Use
Clone this repository to your local machine.
Install dependencies using npm install.
Run the calculator using npm start.
Follow the on-screen prompts to enter two numbers and select an operation.
The result will be displayed in the console.
Features
Supports addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
Uses the Inquirer package for user input.
Written in TypeScript for type safety and better code organization.